description: Goyang was once the place where the Kansai Bridge connecting Hanyang and Uiseong had to pass. The Goyang Lake Park covers an area of 300,000 ping and is the largest artificial lake park in Asia. The freshwater lake of more than 90,000 pings has clear and clean water. The main facilities here include a 4.7-kilometer bicycle lane built along the waterside plaza, artificial islands, etc., as well as a parking lot for 1,050 vehicles, 3 children's playgrounds, a natural learning field, a red-crowned crane breeding ground, The musical fountain, the leisure space composed of more than 100 kinds of wild flowers and more than 200,000 trees, etc., are a good place to learn nature and experience life, and various exhibitions such as the Goyang Flower Expo will be held here.
